    optionB: "Fidaxomicin is a narrow-spectrum macrocyclic antibiotic that inhibits bacterial RNA polymerase (sigma subunit of RNA polymerase) — it has a NARROW spectrum targeting C. difficile while preserving the normal anaerobic gut microbiome (Bacteroides, Prevotella), which provides colonization resistance against C. difficile recurrence. Oral vancomycin disrupts the anaerobic colonic flora more broadly, paradoxically increasing recurrence risk",
