    stem: "A 42-year-old male receiving doxycycline 100mg BID for Lyme disease (early disseminated — facial nerve palsy) also takes ferrous sulfate 325mg daily for iron deficiency anemia. After 5 days, his facial palsy is worsening. Drug levels drawn show subtherapeutic doxycycline. What is the mechanism of tetracycline-class antibiotics, and what caused the treatment failure?",
