    optionD: "Doxycycline binds the 30S ribosomal subunit → blocks aminoacyl-tRNA from entering the A (acceptor) site of the ribosome → prevents codon-anticodon recognition → halts peptide chain elongation → BACTERIOSTATIC. Ferrous sulfate (Fe²⁺) chelates doxycycline in the GI tract, forming insoluble iron-tetracycline complexes → dramatically reduced oral absorption (50-90% reduction) → subtherapeutic serum levels → treatment failure for Lyme disease. Must separate doxycycline from iron by ≥2-3 hours. Other chelating agents: calcium, aluminum/magnesium antacids, dairy, bismuth, zinc",
    correctAnswer: "D",
    rationale: "TETRACYCLINE/DOXYCYCLINE MECHANISM: (1) UPTAKE: Enter Gram-negative bacteria through OmpF and OmpC porin channels in the outer membrane. Cross the inner membrane via energy-dependent transport. (2) 30S RIBOSOMAL BINDING: Bind reversibly to the 16S rRNA component of the 30S ribosomal subunit — specifically at the A-SITE (aminoacyl-tRNA acceptor site). (3) TRANSLATION INHIBITION: Block the binding of aminoacyl-tRNA to the A-site → the ribosome STALLS — cannot add the next amino acid to the growing peptide chain → BACTERIOSTATIC (inhibits growth but does not directly kill). (4) REVERSIBLE: Binding is non-covalent → once drug is removed, ribosomal function resumes. DOXYCYCLINE-SPECIFIC: (1) Lipophilic → excellent oral absorption (~95% bioavailability) and tissue penetration. (2) Long half-life (18-22 hours) → BID dosing. (3) LESS affected by food than older tetracyclines — BUT still significantly chelated by polyvalent cations. IRON CHELATION INTERACTION: Fe²⁺/Fe³⁺ ions form coordinate bonds with the hydroxyl and carbonyl groups of the tetracycline ring system (positions 11, 12, and the amide group) → INSOLUBLE chelate complexes → cannot be absorbed across GI mucosa. Data show 50-90% reduction in doxycycline AUC when co-administered with iron. CLINICAL IMPACT: Subtherapeutic doxycycline for early disseminated Lyme → failure to eradicate Borrelia → progressive cranial nerve palsy, risk of carditis, arthritis. MANAGEMENT: Separate doxycycline from iron by ≥2 hours (give doxycycline first, then iron 2-3 hours later). ALL polyvalent cations chelate tetracyclines: Ca²⁺ (dairy, calcium supplements), Al³⁺/Mg²⁺ (antacids), Fe²⁺/Fe³⁺, Zn²⁺, Bi³⁺ (Pepto-Bismol).",
