    examTip: "Lyme disease treatment: Early localized (erythema migrans): doxycycline 100mg BID × 10-21 days (preferred in adults) or amoxicillin (preferred in pregnancy/children <8). Early disseminated (facial palsy, carditis with mild AV block): oral doxycycline (same dose). Late/neurological (meningitis, severe carditis): IV ceftriaxone 2g daily × 14-28 days. DOXYCYCLINE: avoid in pregnancy (teratogenic — bone/tooth effects) and children <8 (permanent tooth discoloration). Unlike older tetracyclines, doxycycline CAN be taken with food (slight absorption reduction but clinically acceptable — EXCEPT with cation supplements).",
