    examTip: "Ambler classification of beta-lactamases: Class A (serine): TEM, SHV, CTX-M (ESBLs), KPC (carbapenemase). Class B (metallo, Zn²⁺): NDM, VIM, IMP — inhibited by EDTA (chelates zinc), NOT by avibactam. Class C (serine): AmpC — chromosomal (Enterobacter, Citrobacter) or plasmid-mediated. Class D (serine): OXA-type. NEW agents for CRE: Ceftazidime-avibactam (KPC), Meropenem-vaborbactam (KPC), Imipenem-relebactam (KPC + AmpC), Cefiderocol (siderophore — covers MBLs), Aztreonam-avibactam (covers MBL + serine simultaneously).",
