    optionC: "An elevated trough of 3.2 μg/mL (target <1) indicates DRUG ACCUMULATION — the dosing interval is too SHORT relative to the patient's elimination rate, or renal function has declined. The peak of 22 μg/mL is adequate (Cmax/MIC optimization). The elevated trough means: (1) the drug is NOT clearing between doses → sustained exposure of proximal tubular cells to aminoglycoside (megalin-mediated uptake is continuous when drug is present) → INCREASED NEPHROTOXICITY risk, (2) sustained cochlear hair cell exposure → INCREASED OTOTOXICITY risk. Adjustment: EXTEND THE DOSING INTERVAL (e.g., from q24h to q36h or q48h) to allow trough to fall below 1 μg/mL while maintaining the same dose (preserving the adequate peak). Do NOT reduce the dose — this would lower the peak and compromise concentration-dependent killing efficacy",
