    examTip: "Aminoglycoside TDM summary: PEAK too low → INCREASE DOSE (inadequate Cmax/MIC → treatment failure). TROUGH too high → EXTEND INTERVAL (drug accumulation → toxicity). PEAK too high → REDUCE DOSE (risk of concentration-dependent toxicity). TROUGH in range, peak in range → no change. HARTFORD NOMOGRAM: Used for extended-interval dosing — plots 8-12 hour random level on a nomogram to determine 24h/36h/48h interval. CONTRAINDICATIONS to extended-interval dosing: endocarditis (continuous bacteremia needs sustained levels), pregnancy, burns >20% BSA (altered PK), CF (sometimes — many centers still use it with TDM).",
